<voice_0x010012E2><se_def>Angelo: That dog over there's called Boris.
He's the one who dug us out from the snow.

<voice_0x010012E3><se_def>Angelo: What a dog! He's a lot more use than
a certain king, don't you think?
And he smells a bit better too!
<voice_0x010012E4><se_low>King Trode: How dare you, boy! How could you say such a thing about your own master!?
<voice_0x010012E5><se_low>King Trode: Honestly! Who do you think called for the dog's help in the first place!?

<voice_0x010012E6><se_low>King Trode: I heard that, Angelo!
More use than a certain king, you say!?
How dare you!
<voice_0x010012E5><se_low>King Trode: Honestly! Who do you think called for the dog's help in the first place!?
